contentrichtext.text: {{wiktionary}} '''CMO''' is a [[three-letter abbreviation]] that may stand for: ==Business== * [[Chief marketing officer]] * [[Chief Medical Officer (disambiguation)]], the senior government official designated head of medical services ==People and groups== * [[Canadian Mathematical Olympiad]] * [[Chicago, St. Paul, Minneapolis and Omaha Railway]] * [[Chi Mei]] Optoelectronics, producer of TFT LCD panels * [[Commodore's Messenger Organization]], a high-ranking group with the Scientology Sea Organisation * [[Congressional caucus]], or a congressional member organization * [[Contract manufacturing organization]], a pharmaceutical manufacturing outsourcing organization * [[Cyprus Mathematical Olympiad]] ==Science and engineering== *[[Central massive object]] at the center of a galaxy, either a supermassive black hole, or a nuclear star cluster *[[Cetyl myristoleate]], a health supplement *[[Corticosterone 18-monooxygenase]], an enzyme involved in steroid hormone metabolism *[[Cubic Mile of Oil]], a global-scale measure of energy, roughly equal to the amount of oil consumed worldwide each year ==Other uses== * ''[[CAMPUS Magazine Online]]'' * Charter Management Organization, in American education refers to the operator of a [[charter school]] * [[Check Mii Out]], channel for the Wii * [[Civil-military operations]], activities of a military force * [[Collateralized mortgage obligation]] * [[Collective rights management|Collective Management Organization]], typically represent groups of copyright and related rights owners * [[Cripple Mr Onion]], a fictional card game in the Discworld universe {{disambiguation}}
